 already included in the OAuth config. If not, add it to the scopes array wherever Google OAuth is configured. Document this change clearly.\n\n4. **Tool Registration**: Register the new tool in the tool registry so that agents (especially the Manager agent Ananta) can use it. Follow the exact registration pattern used by other tools.\n\n5. **Error Handling**: Return clear error messages if: OAuth token is missing/expired, recipient is invalid, Gmail API returns an error, or required params are missing.\n\n6. **Return Value**: On success, return `{ success: true, messageId: <gmail_message_id>, to: <recipient> }`. On failure, return `{ success: false, error: <error_message> }`.\n\nWrite all necessary files. If you need to modify existing files, show the exact changes (with file paths). Make sure the tool works end-to-end. After writing the code, list all files created/modified and provide a brief summary of how to test it."}]}}

